    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"proven to reduce crime\"? That sounds like a pretty definitive way to put it. I've seen plenty of articles and people saying that crime stays high even where laws are strict, or that criminals just ignore the laws anyway. Isn't that debate still wide open? It feels like you're saying the science is settled when it's actually really controversial.",
